7 An Act relating to the Department of Mental Health
and Substance Abuse Services; making an
8 appropriation; stating purpose; providing an
effective date; and declaring an emergency.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the Department of
13 Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services, from any monies not
14 otherwise appropriated from the Statewide Recovery Fund (497) of the
15 State Treasury, the sum of Fifteen Million Dollars ($15,000,000.00)
16 or so much thereof as may be necessary to address gaps in the
17 project to replace capacity of Griffin Memorial Hospital. Such
18 funds shall be utilized in a manner consistent with the
19 recommendations adopted by the Joint Committee on Pandemic Relief
20 Funding on April 15, 2026.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
22 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
23 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
24
